feat: Enhance BMI Calculator with unit system toggle, detailed categories, and input validation
- Added support for both metric and imperial units with a toggle switch. - Implemented detailed BMI categories with descriptions and health risks. - Improved input validation for height and weight, including range checks. - Introduced error handling and user feedback for invalid inputs. - Enhanced UI with progress bar and healthy weight range display based on height. - Updated layout for better user experience and clarity.

Refactor medical model training and inference pipeline
- Updated model inference to use SentencePiece tokenizer and adjusted paths for tokenizer and answer mapping. - Enhanced model architecture with increased embedding and hidden sizes, and added attention mechanisms. - Replaced TensorFlow with PyTorch for model training, utilizing BERT for improved performance. - Implemented data loading and preprocessing from multiple datasets, ensuring compatibility with new tokenizer. - Introduced early stopping and learning rate scheduling during training for better convergence. - Added logging for better traceability and debugging. - Created a new tokenizer class for handling medical text efficiently. - Updated requirements to include necessary libraries for the new architecture. - Added a README file for documentation and usage instructions.
